{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and line a baking tray (30 cm x 40 cm) with baking paper.","Place almonds in mixing bowl and pulse <nobr>Turbo\/0.5 sec\/3-4 times<\/nobr> until chopped as desired. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place chocolate in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>.","Add desiccated coconut, sugar, reserved chopped almonds, eggs and salt then mix <nobr>1 min\/<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl (see tip).","With wet hands, divide and shape dough into 14 equal-sized balls (about the size of a walnut) and place on prepared baking tray. Flatten with fingers to approx. 1 cm thick.","Bake for 10-15 minutes (180°C) until lightly browned. Leave biscuits to rest on tray for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.","Once cool, serve or store in an airtight container until needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g blanched almonds","80 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa solids), sugar-free, small pieces or callets","100 g desiccated coconut","90 g coconut sugar (see tip)","2 medium eggs","1 pinch pink Himalayan salt"]}],"id":"r267171","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-yIRKsKcMqpo\/XZWqD0-rOkI\/AAAAAAAAfSk\/DYz6oXvX_xUrKdhXgnqc-LbKcHKwMF4sQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_BZhv-JyhX5csU3R7.png","title":"Almond, Coconut and Chocolate Biscuits (No Added Sugar)","publishedAt":"2018-07-23T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"11 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"9 g","calories":"623 kJ \/ 149 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, baking tray (30 cm x 40 cm), airtight container, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Coconut sugar can be found in many large supermarkets or organic food stores.","To get dough off blades, with measuring cup in place, mix <nobr><strong>3 sec\/speed 5<\/strong><\/nobr> and remove dough from sides of mixing bowl."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","35m","14 pieces"]}